This product is an open-core, mixed-licence workspace. The licensing
strategy was settled by operator decision on 2026-06-21 (deliberation
delib-20260620-ca76) and is documented in
docs/adr/092-license-bascule-mpl-to-agpl.md. The split:

- The kernel, persistence/ports, product CLI & runtime, agent engine,
  cockpit/UX, and the multi-tenant federation SERVER are licensed under
  the GNU Affero General Public License, Version 3 only (AGPL-3.0-only).
  See LICENSE-AGPL for the full text, or
  https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html.

- The pure network SDK that third parties link to *talk to* a cosmon
  instance over the wire (cosmon-thin-cli, cosmon-thin-macro,
  cosmon-client) is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0
  (Apache-2.0). See LICENSE-APACHE, or
  http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.

The governing rule — the network-boundary doctrine — is that a crate may
stay Apache-2.0 only if its real `[dependencies]` closure contains zero
AGPL crates (it reaches the AGPL core over the network, never by
code-linking). See the LICENSE file for the rule in full.

