1. Sibling-galaxy crates, vendored in-tree and name-scrubbed under
   ADR-126 §6 (class 2 — in the product closure, so they ship):
     - neurion-core        (Apache-2.0) — registry primitives
     - topon-core          (Apache-2.0) — codebase topology primitives
     - claudion            (Apache-2.0) — Claude bridge primitives
     - apps-transport-http (Apache-2.0) — HTTP-on-Tailscale transport
   These are first-party (authored by the same maintainer) but originate
   in sibling galaxies; they are kept Apache-2.0 as pure network/utility
   libraries consumed by the AGPL product (Apache→consumed-by-AGPL is a
   legal direction).

Third-party crates pulled from crates.io retain their own licenses; the
permissive set admitted into the dependency closure is enumerated and
enforced in deny.toml (`[licenses].allow`) and checked in CI by
`cargo deny check licenses`.

